<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-16555] JIRA Source Component -- Oauth 401 after time</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-16555</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m running the Jira camel k component to get new issues from Jira cloud.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Just a basic&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
from(jira:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//newissues)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After a certain amount of time - (somewhere around 4-5 days), the Jira connector starts throwing 401s.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I get errors like the below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
(Camel (camel-1) thread #0 - jira:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//newIssues) Consumer Consumer[jira://newIssues?accessToken=xxxxxx] failed polling endpoint: jira://newIssues?accessToken=xxxxxx. Will &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; again at next poll. Caused by: [com.atlassian.jira.&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;rest&lt;/span&gt;.client.api.RestClientException - org.codehaus.jettison.json.JSONException: A JSONObject text must begin with &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;{&apos;&lt;/span&gt; at character 1 of oauth_problem=nonce_used]: RestClientException{statusCode=Optional.of(401), errorCollections=[]}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I think the important part here is that the &quot;nonce_used&quot; error from oauth, but not sure what that might mean.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
